text: these are the 10 most livable cities in
the world according to mono.com number
10 Stockholm top-notch education and

number nine is Auckland hosted the Rugby

Gardens are one way the Australian

Mega city is a small town Spirit

Melbourne Australia's cultural Hub is
getting even better with a big push to

Munich where unemployment is low but
failure to act on a few key projects has
hurt its standing its airport needed a
third Runway way to compete with the
other Global cities on this list but did
get one number four is Vienna which
continues to evolve from a beautiful
Relic to a modernized classic affordable
housing there and an imminent brand new
campus for the Vienna University's
school for economics and business will
inject youth into the city number three
is Copenhagen the Danes are the happiest
people on Earth because of places like
this with near perfect integration
between City Life and the outdoors the
city aims to be carbon neutral by 202
five number two is Helsinki Finland
crowned World design capital in 2012 it
is unveiling a new metro line and
converting its Harbors into attractive
residential areas it's a city where good
ideas can quickly come to life and
number one is Zurich with 50 impressive
museums concert halls and theaters and a
strict corporate culture this clean
beautiful city is one larger cities
should learn from in the end the cities
that made the cut are not just okay but
places that are benchmarks for urban
Renaissance and rigorous reinvention and
everything from Environmental Policy to
Transportation notably no City in the
Americas made the top 10 and no city in
South America or Africa made the top 25
